### Universal Object Model (UOM)

Status: Foundation started.

Completed:
- `connectors/uom.py` — canonical object composition layer
- Canonical object schema: id, type, name, display_name, description, owner, market, version, status, warnings, _links, _relationships, _graph, _metadata
- Field object support with full relationship set (records, pages, components, peoplecode, search_records, views, sql)
- UOM-to-object-renderer adapter for the Object Explorer
- Field graph provider built from UOM relationship set

Completed additions (2026-06-29):
- **Operator → UOM**: `operator_object()`, `sections_for_operator()`, `operator_payload()` in `uom.py`;
  `/api/peoplesoft/object/operator/{name}` now UOM-driven. Sections: Identity / Roles / Permission Lists /
  Graph Preview / Warnings. Graph: operator → roles (up to 20), operator → permission lists (up to 20).
  `_links` includes `explorer` → `/admin/operator/{oprid}` and `tracing` → `/admin/tracing?oprid={oprid}`.
- **Role → UOM**: `role_object()`, `sections_for_role()`, `role_payload()` in `uom.py`;
  `/api/peoplesoft/object/role/{name}` now UOM-driven. Sections: Definition / Members / Permission Lists /
  Graph Preview / Warnings. Graph: role → members (up to 20), role → permission lists (up to 15).
  `_links` includes `explorer` → `/admin/role/{rolename}`.
- **Fix `attach_graph_context` idempotency**: guards against adding duplicate "Knowledge Graph Neighbors"
  section when called on an already-enriched payload (happens at route level for all UOM types).

Remaining:
- Migrate Permission List, Component, Page into full UOM providers (lower priority — ad-hoc payloads work)
- Move Graph Explorer to consume UOM graph providers for every object type
- Add shared UOM relationship provider registration
- Add UOM schemas for Integration Broker, Query, Tree, CI, Portal objects

