### Knowledge Graph Engine

Status: Foundation complete.

Completed:
- `connectors/graphdb.py` — in-memory graph backend with JSON persistence
- Node model: id, type, name, display_name, metadata, canonical URL, icon, warnings
- Typed edges: USES, CONTAINS, BELONGS_TO, CALLS, CALLED_BY, REFERENCES, REFERENCED_BY, SECURES, EXPOSES, OWNS, DEPENDS_ON, GENERATES, READS, WRITES
- Incremental provider-based graph builder using connector/UOM metadata
- Providers: operators, roles, permission lists, components, pages, fields, PeopleCode, AE programs
- Graph algorithms: neighbors, shortest path, dependency tree, reverse dependency, connected components, cycle detection, topological ordering
- Graph exports: JSON, GraphML, DOT
- REST APIs under `/api/graph`
- `/admin/graphdb` diagnostics UI
- Object Explorer enriches payloads with Knowledge Graph neighbors

Remaining:
- Add graph providers for Integration Broker, Query, Tree, CI, Portal, SQL
- Add graph diff/snapshot support for Environment Compare integration
- Add graph compaction/indexing for large environments
- Richer security traversal APIs (why-user-has-access path)

