### PeopleCode Explorer

Status: Foundation implemented.

Completed:
- `connectors/peoplecode.py` — grant-aware PeopleCode discovery
- PeopleCode registered as canonical object type in Metadata Registry
- Canonical URLs: `/admin/object/peoplecode/{encoded_reference}`, `/api/peoplesoft/peoplecode/{encoded_reference}`
- Source reconstruction where PSPCMTXT is readable
- Best-effort reference extraction: records, fields, components, SQL definitions, functions/calls, application packages/classes, application engines, service operations
- Best-effort call extraction: SQLExec, CreateSQL, GetSQL, CallAppEngine, Transfer, DoModal, CreateRecord, GetRecord, GetField, MessageBox, and others
- PeopleCode graph provider added to Knowledge Graph builder
- Object Explorer renders PeopleCode objects with source blocks
- Global Search includes PeopleCode results

Completed additions (2026-06-29 pass 2):
- **Event label decoding**: `PEOPLECODE_EVENTS` set + `extract_event()` in `peoplecode.py` scans
  objectvalue columns right-to-left for known event names (FieldChange, RowInit, SavePreChange,
  Activate, OnExecute, etc.); correctly handles Record/Component/AE/Page PC structures.
- **Object type label**: `PEOPLECODE_OBJECT_TYPES` dict maps objectid1 → "Record"/"Component"/etc.;
  `_OID1_PARENT_TYPES` derives parent_type/parent_name from objectid1+objectvalue1 when reference-based
  detection misses (e.g., bare "RECNAME.FIELD.EVENT.0" references).
- **`program()` lookup fix**: now searches PSPCMPROG by first reference component (object name) with
  limit=500, then filters for exact reference match — previously the full dotted reference never
  matched any single column, leaving all metadata as None in the Object Explorer.
- **`programs()` bind var fix**: removed `"limit"` from Oracle bind params (it was f-string
  interpolated into the SQL, not a `:limit` placeholder); DPY-4008 error is gone, search works.
- **PeopleCode Metadata section**: now shows curated fields (reference, object_type, event,
  parent_type, parent_name, last_updated, updated_by) instead of raw objectvalue dump.
- **PeopleCode syntax highlighting**: `highlightPeopleCode()` in admin.py tokenizes source for
  block comments (/* */), string literals, keywords (If/Else/For/Function/…), and built-in
  function calls (SQLExec/GetRecord/CallAppEngine/…); colors applied via inline `<span>` styles.

Completed additions (2026-06-29 pass 3):
- **objectid1 labels corrected**: Data-driven discovery; confirmed actual PeopleTools types in this database:
  1=Record, 3=Menu, 9=Component (event-level), 10=Component (record/field-level), 60=Subscription (IB old-style),
  66=Application Engine, 74=Component Interface, 104=Handler (IB new-style). `PEOPLECODE_OBJECT_TYPES` and
  `_OID1_PARENT_TYPES` updated to match; parent links now correctly route to AE/Service Operation/CI pages.
- **AE PeopleCode linkage**: Resolved — objectid1=66 is AE PeopleCode. `ae_peoplecode()` fixed to query
  `WHERE OBJECTID1=66 AND OBJECTVALUE1=:ae_applid`. 2118 distinct AE programs have PeopleCode in this env.
- **IB PeopleCode type labels**: 60=Subscription, 104=Handler; parent_type correctly set to "service_operation"

Remaining:
- Full Application Package/Class parsing (objectid1 for true AppPkg class methods not yet identified in this env)
- SQL text object pages and SQL-to-record dependency extraction
- Precise PeopleCode-to-component/page/action mapping when metadata grants are available
- Large-source pagination (max 114 lines in current env; low priority)

