### Transaction Tracing

Status: Foundation implemented (2026-06-29).

Architecture:
- Correlates activity across three data sources keyed by OPRID:
  PSACCESSLOG (login history), PSPRCSRQST (process scheduler), V$SESSION (Oracle, via CLIENT_IDENTIFIER).
- IB transaction correlation via PSAPMSGPUBHDR.PUBLISHER attempted; degrades when table is inaccessible.
- Unified timeline sorted newest-first; each event carries type, status, title, detail, and links.

Completed:
- `connectors/tracing.py`:
  - `operator_search(env, q, limit)` — PSOPRDEFN search for autocomplete
  - `access_history(env, oprid, hours_back)` — PSACCESSLOG login/logout history by OPRID
  - `recent_active_operators(env, limit)` — operators active in the last 24h (sidebar)
  - `process_history(env, oprid, hours_back)` — PSPRCSRQST runs by OPRID + time window
  - `oracle_sessions_for_oprid(db, oprid)` — V$SESSION where CLIENT_IDENTIFIER = OPRID
  - `ib_transactions_for_oprid(env, oprid, hours_back)` — PSAPMSGPUBHDR by PUBLISHER
  - `trace(env, db, oprid, hours_back)` — unified timeline merging all sources; summary counts
- `routers/tracing.py` — 7 GET endpoints under `/api/tracing/`:
  - `GET /api/tracing/config` — envs and dbs
  - `GET /api/tracing/operators` — autocomplete search
  - `GET /api/tracing/active` — recent active operators (sidebar data)
  - `GET /api/tracing/trace` — unified trace for an OPRID
  - `GET /api/tracing/sessions` — access log only
  - `GET /api/tracing/processes` — process scheduler only
  - `GET /api/tracing/oracle` — Oracle session correlation only
- `/admin/tracing` UI:
  - Topbar: env + DB selectors, OPRID input with live autocomplete from PSOPRDEFN, hours range, Trace button
  - Sidebar: recently active operators (last 24h) — click to trace immediately
  - Main: summary stat boxes (logins / processes / errors / Oracle sessions / IB txns)
  - Vertical timeline: color-coded event cards (login=green, process=cyan, oracle=purple, IB=amber)
  - Each card expandable: full key-value detail, SQL text block for Oracle events, status chips
  - Filter buttons: All / Logins / Processes / Oracle / IB; Expand All / Collapse

Limitations:
- PSACCESSLOG not accessible in this environment (HCM deathstar_admin lacks grant);
  login/logout timeline events not available; operator autocomplete and process history work fine
- V$SESSION CLIENT_IDENTIFIER correlation depends on PeopleSoft setting it at the app server level;
  may return empty if the application server doesn't populate CLIENT_IDENTIFIER
- No historical Oracle session data (ASH requires Diagnostics Pack license)
- IB correlation requires PSAPMSGPUBHDR grant (currently inaccessible)

