## Next Recommended Slice

**FSCM Field Types + Record Index Explorer + Global Search — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- **FSCM Field Types in Field Explorer**: `field_definition()` now falls through to a PSDBFIELD-only
  query when called without record context, returning `field_type` + `length` from PSDBFIELD when
  accessible. `loadField()` in `/admin/field` now fetches definition in parallel with records and
  populates `fieldTypeChip` (e.g. "Char") and `fieldLenChip` (e.g. "Len 11"); both chips are empty
  in HCM (graceful degradation). New chip CSS: `.chip-def`, `.chip-len`.

- **FSCM Record Index Explorer**: `renderIndexes(indexes, keys)` in `/admin/record` now accepts both
  PSINDEXDEFN rows and PSKEYDEFN rows, shows uniqueflag/activeflag/custkeyorder badges, groups key
  field composition (with ▼ for DESC) by index ID with labels (PK/Primary Search/Alt Search A–Z).
  `renderKeys()` fixed to use actual PSKEYDEFN columns: indexid/keyposn/fieldname/ascdesc (was
  using wrong field names: fieldnum/keytype/searchkey/duporder). `loadTab('indexes')` now fetches
  both `/indexes` and `/keys` in parallel via `Promise.all`.

- **Global Search enhancement**: `global_search()` in `ptmetadata.py` now filters out `error: True`
  entries (inaccessible types) — clean results only. `/admin/object` `objectUrl()` now routes
  `operator` → `/admin/operator/{name}`, `role` → `/admin/role/{name}`, `record` → `/admin/record/{name}`
  for direct navigation to dedicated explorer UIs. `globalSearch()` rendering upgraded: type-colored
  chips per object type, monospace names, status shows accessible count + inaccessible type count.

**Record → UOM canonical page — implemented (2026-06-29)**

`record_object()` / `sections_for_record()` / `record_payload()` added to `connectors/uom.py`.
`/api/peoplesoft/object/record/{name}` now driven by UOM. Full section set: Definition, Fields,
Keys, Indexes, Related Records, Components, Pages, Storage, Graph Preview, Warnings — all
grant-aware. Graph includes record → fields (capped at 30), parent → record, record → component.

**Operator → UOM / Role → UOM / Object Explorer Recently Viewed — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `operator_object()` / `role_object()` and their payload/sections functions added to `connectors/uom.py`
- `canonical_object()` routes `operator` and `role` types to UOM; both `_links` include `explorer` deep-link
- `attach_graph_context()` made idempotent — guards against duplicate "Knowledge Graph Neighbors" section
- Object Explorer `/admin/object`: "Recently Viewed" localStorage panel (last 12 objects, type chips,
  persists across sessions, Clear button); `TYPE_CHIP_CFG` constant shared between recent list and
  search results; `pushRecent()` called on every `loadObject()` call

**Permission List → UOM / adaptive PSAUTHITEM security traversal — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `permissionlist_object()` / `sections_for_permissionlist()` / `permissionlist_payload()` added to
  `connectors/uom.py`; `/api/peoplesoft/object/permissionlist/{name}` now uses UOM. Sections:
  Definition / Roles / Menus / Components / Graph Preview / Warnings. Graph includes role →
  permission list and permission list → component edges.
- `permission_list` remains a compatibility alias for object lookups, but canonical links now use
  `permissionlist`.
- `psdb.auth_component_source()` added for PeopleTools schema variation: uses `PSAUTHITEM.PNLGRPNAME`
  when available, or resolves `PSAUTHITEM.PNLITEMNAME` through `PSPNLGROUP.PNLNAME` to derive the
  component. This fixed permission-list components, component permission lists, component access,
  operator components, and component menu placements in the current HCM/FSCM schemas.
- Confirmed examples: HCM `CRM8000` resolves 1 role, 8 menus, 7 components; FSCM `ALLPAGES` resolves
  13 roles, 8,295 menus, 37,401 component grants.

**Security Explanation — first slice implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `psdb.explain_operator_component_access(env, oprid, component)` added. It explains operator →
  role → permission list → component access using the now-adaptive `PSAUTHITEM` traversal. The result
  includes `has_access`, grant paths, matching permission lists, role/permission-list/component counts,
  and warnings for degraded relationship lookups.
- `GET /api/peoplesoft/security/explain?env=HCM&oprid={oprid}&component={component}` added.
- `/admin/security` now has an "Explain Access" action that uses the existing OPRID and component
  inputs to show grant paths when access exists, or the operator/component permission-list mismatch
  when it does not.
- Confirmed examples: `GUACUSER` → `GDP_SELECT_PRCS` returns 3 visible grant paths; `VP1` →
  `GDP_SELECT_PRCS` returns no visible path and zero matching permission lists.
- `attach_links()` corrected so component rows with `searchrecname` still link to the component
  canonical page instead of being mistaken for record rows.

**PeopleCode semantic path decoding — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `connectors/peoplecode.py` now emits richer normalized metadata for PSPCMPROG rows:
  `event_label`, `event_scope`, `subtype`, `semantic_path`, and `semantic_path_text`.
- Decoder is object-type aware for the observed PeopleTools structures:
  - Record field PeopleCode: `record / field / event`
  - Menu item PeopleCode: `menu / menu item slot / menu item / event`
  - Component event PeopleCode: `component / event`
  - Component record/field PeopleCode: `component / market / record / field / event`
  - IB subscription/handler PeopleCode: `service operation / handler or subscription / event`
  - Application Engine PeopleCode: `AE / section / market / DB type / effective date / step / event`
  - Component Interface PeopleCode: `CI / event or methods`
- Added event labels for `ItemSelected` and `OnSelect`; existing labels are normalized to readable
  PeopleCode casing.
- Object Explorer PeopleCode metadata and `/admin/peoplecode` detail view now show scope, subtype,
  and semantic path.
- Confirmed examples: `AAP_YEAR` record-field events, `ABS_CAL_POPUP` menu item `ItemSelected`,
  `AA_MGMT_JPN` component record/field events, `AA_CONV_JPN` AE `OnExecute`, `ACCOUNT_CHARTFIELD_SYNC`
  IB handler/subscription, and `CI_GROUP_INCR_BUDGET` CI methods.

**Integration Broker graph expansion — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `connectors/graphdb.py` Integration Broker provider now adds richer relationships:
  service operation → routing (`ROUTES`), routing → service operation (`BELONGS_TO`), sender node →
  routing, routing → receiver node, routing → queue, service operation → queue, and service operation
  → attached IB PeopleCode.
- Traditional service operations discovered through `PSIBRTNGDEFN.IB_OPERATIONNAME` are tracked even
  when they do not exist as PSIBAPPLDEFN application services; attached handler/subscription
  PeopleCode is added via `ib.service_peoplecode()`.
- Small non-persisted HCM graph build with `limit=20` completed with no graph warnings:
  861 nodes / 1,422 edges, including 33 service operations, 20 routings, 20 queues, 28 nodes, and
  32 PeopleCode nodes.

**Environment Compare graph snapshot diff — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `graphdb.diff(env1, env2, node_types=None, limit=200)` added. It compares current/persisted
  `knowledge_graph_<ENV>.json` snapshots by node id and edge id, returning:
  only-in-env1 nodes/edges, only-in-env2 nodes/edges, metadata-changed nodes, metadata-changed edges,
  summary counts, snapshot build timestamps, paths, and warnings for missing/empty snapshots.
- REST endpoints added:
  - `GET /api/graph/diff?env1=HCM&env2=FSCM&node_types=record,component&limit=200`
  - `GET /api/envcompare/graph?env1=HCM&env2=FSCM&node_types=record,component&limit=200`
- `/admin/envcompare` now has a **Graph** tab with node-type filter, snapshot warnings/build links,
  summary stat boxes, and expandable sections for node/edge differences.
- Verification:
  - Empty/missing FSCM persisted graph returns a structured `graph_snapshot_empty` warning.
  - Non-persisted paired build with `limit=15`: HCM 655 nodes / 1,033 edges, FSCM 700 nodes /
  1,202 edges, zero graph warnings. Filtered graph diff returned 246 HCM nodes vs 234 FSCM nodes,
  23 common nodes, 20 changed nodes, and no warnings.

**Security Explanation page/menu slice — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `psdb.explain_operator_page_access(env, oprid, page)` added. It resolves page → component(s), then
  composes the existing component-access explanation for each component. Results include visible
  component matches, grant paths, decoded action modes, warnings, and a human explanation string.
- `psdb.explain_operator_menu_access(env, oprid, menu)` added. It explains operator → role →
  permission list → menu paths from `PSROLEUSER` / `PSROLECLASS` / `PSAUTHITEM`.
- REST endpoints added:
  - `GET /api/peoplesoft/security/explain-page?env=HCM&oprid={oprid}&page={page}`
  - `GET /api/peoplesoft/security/explain-menu?env=HCM&oprid={oprid}&menu={menu}`
- `/admin/security` now has **Explain Page** and **Explain Menu** actions using the existing OPRID
  and target input. Results show matching components, grant paths, permission lists, menus, and pages.
- Confirmed examples:
  - `GUACUSER` → page `GDP_SELECT_PRCS`: access through 1 component and 3 grant paths
  - `VP1` → page `GDP_SELECT_PRCS`: no visible component access path
  - `GUACUSER` → menu `MANAGE_GUIDED_PROCESS`: 13 visible role/permission-list/menu paths
  - `VP1` → menu `MANAGE_GUIDED_PROCESS`: no visible role/permission-list/menu path

**Graph snapshot operations — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- Added named graph snapshots under `data/graph_snapshots/` with `manifest.json` tracking snapshot id,
  env, name, note, created time, graph build time, node/edge counts, warning count, and file path.
- `connectors/graphdb.py` additions:
  - `create_snapshot(env, name, note)`
  - `list_snapshots(env=None)`
  - `load_snapshot(snapshot_id)`
  - `delete_snapshot(snapshot_id)`
  - `diff_snapshots(snapshot1, snapshot2, node_types=None, limit=200)`
- REST endpoints added:
  - `POST /api/graph/snapshots?env=HCM&name={name}&note={note}`
  - `GET /api/graph/snapshots?env=HCM`
  - `GET /api/graph/snapshots/{snapshot_id}`
  - `DELETE /api/graph/snapshots/{snapshot_id}`
  - `GET /api/graph/snapshot-diff?snapshot1={id1}&snapshot2={id2}`
- `/admin/graphdb` now has snapshot controls: create snapshot, refresh list, open JSON, delete.
- Existing latest-graph behavior remains unchanged (`data/knowledge_graph_<ENV>.json` still backs
  `/api/graph/stats`, export, search, and default diff).
- Verification: connector and HTTP route checks created/listed/loaded/diffed/deleted temporary HCM
  snapshots successfully; same-snapshot diff returned 104 common nodes / 196 common edges and no changes.
- Follow-up UI completed: `/admin/graphdb` can now select two named snapshots, optionally filter by
  node type, run `snapshot-diff`, and render summary counts plus sample changed/only-in nodes.

**Security Explanation field-level page details — implemented (2026-06-29)**

- `psdb.explain_operator_page_access()` now includes page field metadata from `PSPNLFIELD` and counts:
  total fields, visible fields, invisible fields, and display-only fields.
- `GET /api/peoplesoft/security/explain-page` returns linked field rows, so the explanation can jump
  from page security to canonical field/record context.
- `/admin/security` **Explain Page** results now show the page plus a sample of page fields with
  record.field, label, Invisible, and Display Only indicators.
- Confirmed example: `GUACUSER` → page `GDP_SELECT_PRCS` returns 17 fields, all visible, with 3
  component grant paths.

